TELC:sample.name: MINOR_VERSION
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Release version starting from 0x1 (0x0 indicates unreleased, in addition to platform version, for compatibility) per major version. Does NOT re-start for stepping. 0x0 - Silicon others TBD (>=0x8 expected to be pre-Si such as VP or (H)SLE if format or compile flags are different) 0xB - Release pre-Si version (e.g. ifwi load testing). 0xC - Unreleased CI/CD (i.e. gatekeeper) SOC compile. 0xD - Unreleased CI/CD (i.e. gatekeeper) PUNIT compile. 0xE - Unrelease CI/CD (i.e. gatekeeper) PCODE compile.0xF - Unreleased user build

TELC:sample.name: PLATFORM_VERSION
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Platform target of compile 0x0 - Silicon others TBD (>=0x8 expected to be pre-Si such as VP or (H)SLE if format or compile flags are different) 0xB - Release pre-Si version (e.g. ifwi load testing) 0xC - Unreleased CI/CD (i.e. gatekeeper) SOC compile 0xD - Unreleased CI/CD (i.e. gatekeeper) PUNIT compile 0xE - Unrelease CI/CD (i.e. gatekeeper) PCODE compile 0xF - Unreleased user build

TELC:sample.name: STEPPING_VERSION
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Silicon stepping group (grouped by compatible hardware, i.e. if the same PCODE compile can run on A1 or B0 they will have the same STEPPING_VERSION)

TELC:sample.name: MAJOR_VERSION
TELC:sample.TELC:description: New version for each product (Elasti X2, X3, compute, etc.) starting with 1 (0 is invalid indication)

TELC:sample.name: ENGINEERING_VERSION
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Must be 0 for productionn-releasedd builds For debug, hotfix, release candidate etc. builds (which have a MINOR_VERSION) - First 28 bits are last 6 digits of owner's WWID without conversion from decimal to hex (e.g. 11305524->0x305524) - Lowest nibble (4 bits) is a user increment within the respective major/minor version For unreleased CI/CD builds (platform 0xC ~ 0xE): - All 32 bits will be the first 8 bits of the most recent commit SHA (sufficient to find a git commit in the history) in the repo of the subsystem where it was compiled For user unreleased builds (Platform 0xF): - First 28 bits are last 6 digits of owner's WWID without conversion from decimal to hex (e.g. 11305524->0x305524) - Lowest nibble (4 bits) is 0 if there are uncommitted changes in the repo or the first two MSB of the most recent commits SHA in the repo (this is NOT sufficient to find the commit in the history, but enough to identify recent commits through reflog etc.).
